frameDefinitions: An Agent finishes an Activity, which can no longer logically continue.
A Process comes to an end.
A Material has been processed (generally industrially) to some Degree in order to make it more useful for some (usually implicit) function.

A Cognizer possesses knowledge about the workings, significance, or meaning of an idea or object, which we call Phenomenon, and is able to make predictions about the behavior or  occurrence of the Phenomenon.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
Through use, a Resource is diminished in quality or quantity (up to complete attrition) such that it becomes less capable of sustaining future use.
frameExamples: Jason <t>completed</t> grading the papers late Sunday night.
I figured this out last week and now I really <t>understand</t> it.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
My entire life savings is <t>depleted</t> due to university and medical bills.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Agent</fen> who has finished an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> has finished.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> finishes.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> finishes the <fen>Activity</fen>.
Name of the event which occurs.
The substance which is altered in some useful way.
The sentient animate being who acquires new knowledge.
A state of affairs or dynamic system whose internal make-up and working the Cognizer comes to assimilate into their knowledge structure.
A part  of a person's cognitive-emotional faculties that is said to acquire knowledge.
This role indicates the when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> asssimilates the new knowledge.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The <fen>Resource</fen> is a physical entity or an ability to perform work that was used in an earlier process, typically in pursuit of a goal.
listRoleExamples: You must grasp <fex>the complex relationship of all these subjects to each other</fex>
<fex>Yesterday</fex> the students finally grasped the meaning of the equation
Stu treated <fex>the lumber</fex> with magical waterproofing fairydust.
